Four people, 2 adults and 2 children, were killed in a tragic road accident on the N3 highway 20km outside Harrismith, earlier today.At the time of publishing authorities did not release the cause of the accident, however it is understood that a tanker carrying diesel and 3 light motor vehicles were involved, resulting in the terrible blaze.It is further understood that a family from Roshnee, Gauteng, were lucky to escape the accident with little or no injuries, after their car was written off.